Ashland Community and Technical College ( ACTC ) , located in Ashland , KY , is one of 16 two - year , open - admissions colleges of the Kentucky Community and Technical College System ( KCTCS ) . It is accredited by the Southern Association of Colleges and Schools ( SACS ) to offer numerous certificates and associate degrees . Three campuses encompass the ACTC system . The College Drive Campus is located near downtown Ashland near 13th Street and is where business , education , hospital - related , and information technology degrees are offered . The Roberts Drive Campus , located at the southern edge of Ashland , offers several industrial technology degrees . It will ultimately be replaced with the Technology Drive Campus . The new Technology Drive Campus offers numerous industrial technology degrees that often reflect the job stock in the Ashland region . It is located on the KY 67 ( Industrial Parkway ) in extreme southern Greenup County . This Kentucky school - related article is a stub . 